FBIS4-17443 "drsov079_r_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 Azerbaijan Aliyev Postpones Trip Due to War Escalation Aliyev Postpones Trip Due to War Escalation NC2304195594 Baku TURAN in English 1723 GMT 23 Apr 94 NC2304195594 Baku TURAN English BFN [Text] Baku, April 23 (TURAN) -- "Azeri President Geydar Aliyev has been forced to postpone his visit to Brussels due to the escalation of Armenian aggression", said the Presidential apparat's press-service. The visit, which was planned on April 26, was put off for a week. During the visit, Azerbaijan's participation in NATO's programme, "Partnership for the sake of peace", will be discussed. Last week, during the press-conference, Azeri Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov told journalists that "the possibility of Azerbaijan's joining the NATO programme is being reviewed by the Azeri Government and Azerbaijan will give its final answer in the near future.
